|image=PIA16239 High-Resolution Self-Portrait by Curiosity Rover Arm Camera.jpg
|title=[[Curiosity (rover)]]
|texttitle=Curiosity (rover)
|size=300
|caption=

A self-portrait by the [[Mars]] rover '''''[[Curiosity (rover)|Curiosity]]''''' on October 31, 2012. The mosaic is stitched from a set of 55 images taken by the [[Mars Hand Lens Imager]] at "Rocknest," the spot in [[Gale (crater)|Gale crater]] where [[Mars Science Laboratory|the mission's]] first scoop sampling took place. Self-portraits such as this help [[NASA]] document the state of the rover and track changes, such as dust accumulation and wheel wear.

|credit=Photograph: [[NASA]]
